As for the /hmofa/ bit, this is seen by the multitude of non-human races in the world.
While there are a few non-anthros, like orcs and dwarves, two of the biggest players are anthro
>Cynocephali
Commonly abbreviated to Cyno's, the vast majority of Cynocephali serve under Thousand-Horns, the lord of the wild. A (supposed) forest god from another realm, he maintains a belief which could largely be considered anarcho-primitivist, considering the collapse of industrial society great. As such, he employs his followers to destroy all traces of the old world, and quell any attempts to resurrect it. The Cynos have wolves heads, but otherwise are human shaped (elf actually), and can bring deadly pagan magics against those they deem enemies of the wild.
The love interest would be a young, rather inexperienced druidess, who is tasked with being an emissary of Thousand-Horns to the greater world.
>Gnolls
Gnolls are the subject of convergent evolution, literally being bipedal descendants of some hyena-like species. They stand far taller and larger than most humans, at 6'10 on average with the matriarch, the leader of each pack, reaching 8ft. For the most part, they live in nomadic tribes(Gnolls are a social species, and solitude is far worse for their mental state than it is humans). The exception to this is the Sak'yiira Dynasty. Led by a startling intelligent, 10ft tall behemoth of a gnoll (Sak'yiira, they have set about creating a small, if technologically advanced society far from nearly anyone. Rumors abound of their patrols scrapping old airframes, and strange sounds coming from the night sky above their territory.
The main love interest would be a traumatised, cynical gnoll who was the sole survivor of her pack being wiped out. What starts out as a relatively antagonistic, if combat-capable party member slowly warms, to become one of your most loyal and steadfast allies, and lovers, if you wish.

Naturally, you can see how the two would have a bit of tension.
